\end_inset

 be a probability space.
 An rv 
\begin_inset Formula $X:\Omega\rightarrow\mathbb{R}$
\end_inset

 is 
\begin_inset Formula $\text{n}\left(m,\sigma^{2}\right)$
\end_inset

 if the distribution of 
\begin_inset Formula $X$
\end_inset

 has a density of the form
\begin_inset Formula 
\[
p_{X}\left(x\right)=\frac{1}{\sqrt{2\pi\sigma^{2}}}e^{-\frac{\left(x-m\right)^{2}}{2\sigma^{2}}}
\]

\end_inset

In other words 
\begin_inset Formula 
\begin{eqnarray*}
P\left[X\in G\right] & = & \int_{G}p_{X}\left(x\right)dx\\
 & = & \int_{G}I_{G}dP
\end{eqnarray*}

\end_inset

for all Borel sets 
\begin_inset Formula $G\subset\mathbb{R}$
\end_inset

.
 
\end_layout

\begin_layout Definition
Then 
\begin_inset Formula 
\[
E\left[X\right]=\int_{\Omega}XdP=\int_{\mathbb{R}}xp_{X}\left(x\right)dx=m
\]

\end_inset

and 
\begin_inset Formula 
\[
\text{Var}\left(X\right)=E\left[\left(X-m\right)^{2}\right]=\int_{\mathbb{R}}\left(x-m\right)^{2}p_{X}\left(x\right)dx=\sigma^{2}
\]

