\begin_inset Formula 
\[
p_{X}\left(x_{1},\dots,x_{n}\right)=\frac{1}{\sqrt[n]{2\pi\left|\Sigma^{-1}\right|}}e^{-\frac{1}{2}\left(\mathbf{x}-\mathbf{m}\right)^{T}\Sigma^{-1}\left(\mathbf{x}-\mathbf{m}\right)}
\]

\end_inset

where 
\begin_inset Formula $E\left[X\right]=\mathbf{m}$
\end_inset

 and 
\begin_inset Formula $\Sigma_{jk}^{-1}=E\left[\left(X_{j}-m_{j}\right)\left(X_{k}-m_{k}\right)\right]$
\end_inset

 is the covariance matrix of 
\begin_inset Formula $X$
\end_inset

.
