\begin_layout Theorem
Let 
\begin_inset Formula 
\[
dX_{t}=udt+vdB_{t}
\]

\end_inset

be an n-dimensional Ito process and 
\begin_inset Formula $g\left(t,X\right)=\left(g_{1}\left(t,X\right),\dots,g_{p}\left(t,X\right)\right)$
\end_inset

 be 
\begin_inset Formula $C^{2}$
\end_inset

 map from 
\begin_inset Formula $\left[0,\infty\right)\times\mathbb{R}^{n}\rightarrow\mathbb{R}^{p}$
\end_inset

.
 Then
\begin_inset Formula 
\[
Y_{t}=g\left(t,X_{t}\right)
\]

\end_inset

is an Ito process whose components abide by the Ito formula
\begin_inset Formula 
\[
dY_{k}=\frac{\partial g_{k}}{\partial t}dt+\left(\nabla g\right)\cdot\left(dX\right)+\frac{1}{2}dX\cdot H_{g}\cdot dX
\]

\end_inset

where 
\begin_inset Formula $dB_{t,i}dB_{t,j}=\delta_{i,j}dt$
\end_inset

 and 
\begin_inset Formula $dB_{t,i}dt=dtdB_{t,i}=0$
\end_inset

.
\end_layout

